Document: RDSamplerState
Path: godot/classes/class_rdsamplerstate.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for configuring a sampler state in the RenderingDevice.

Properties:
* anisotropy_max (float): Maximum anisotropy level. Default: 1.0
* border_color (SamplerBorderColor): The color used for border clamping. Default: 2
* compare_op (CompareOperator): The comparison operator used when depth comparison is enabled. Default: 7
* enable_compare (bool): Enables depth comparison. Default: false
* lod_bias (float): Bias applied to the Level of Detail calculation. Default: 0.0
* mag_filter (SamplerFilter): The filter used when sampling textures when magnified. Default: 0
* max_lod (float): Maximum Level of Detail. Default: 1e+20
* min_filter (SamplerFilter): The filter used when sampling textures when minified. Default: 0
* min_lod (float): Minimum Level of Detail. Default: 0.0
* mip_filter (SamplerFilter): The filter used when sampling between mipmap levels. Default: 0
* repeat_u (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode for the U coordinate. Default: 2
* repeat_v (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode for the V coordinate. Default: 2
* repeat_w (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode for the W coordinate. Default: 2
* unnormalized_uvw (bool): If true, UVW coordinates are not normalized to [0, 1]. Default: false
* use_anisotropy (bool): Enables anisotropic filtering. Default: false
