Document: RDSamplerState
Path: godot/classes/class_rdsamplerstate.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the RDSamplerState class, which control how textures are sampled in the RenderingDevice.

Property Descriptions
anisotropy_max (float): Maximum anisotropy that can be used when sampling. Only effective if use_anisotropy is true. Higher values result in a sharper sampler at oblique angles, at the cost of performance. This value may be limited by graphics hardware, typically up to 16.0. If anisotropy_max is 1.0, anisotropy is disabled even if use_anisotropy is true. Default: 1.0.
Method: set_anisotropy_max(value: float)
Method: get_anisotropy_max() -> float

border_color (SamplerBorderColor): The border color that will be returned when sampling outside the sampler's bounds and the repeat modes are disabled. Default: 2.
Method: set_border_color(value: SamplerBorderColor)
Method: get_border_color() -> SamplerBorderColor

compare_op (CompareOperator): The compare operation to use. Only effective if enable_compare is true. Default: 7.
Method: set_compare_op(value: CompareOperator)
Method: get_compare_op() -> CompareOperator

enable_compare (bool): If true, returned values will be based on the comparison operation defined in compare_op. This is a hardware-based approach and is therefore faster than performing this manually in a shader. For example, compare operations are used for shadow map rendering by comparing depth values from a shadow sampler. Default: false.
Method: set_enable_compare(value: bool)
Method: get_enable_compare() -> bool

lod_bias (float): The mipmap LOD bias to use. Positive values make the sampler blurrier, while negative values make it sharper (at the risk of looking grainy). Recommended values are between -0.5 and 0.0. Only effective if the sampler has mipmaps available. Default: 0.0.
Method: set_lod_bias(value: float)
Method: get_lod_bias() -> float

mag_filter (SamplerFilter): The sampler's magnification filter. It is the filtering method used when sampling texels that appear bigger than on-screen pixels. Default: 0.
Method: set_mag_filter(value: SamplerFilter)
Method: get_mag_filter() -> SamplerFilter

max_lod (float): The maximum mipmap LOD bias to display (lowest resolution). Only effective if the sampler has mipmaps available. Default: 1e+20.
Method: set_max_lod(value: float)
Method: get_max_lod() -> float

min_filter (SamplerFilter): The sampler's minification filter. It is the filtering method used when sampling texels that appear smaller than on-screen pixels. Default: 0.
Method: set_min_filter(value: SamplerFilter)
Method: get_min_filter() -> SamplerFilter

min_lod (float): The minimum mipmap LOD bias to display (highest resolution). Only effective if the sampler has mipmaps available. Default: 0.0.
Method: set_min_lod(value: float)
Method: get_min_lod() -> float

mip_filter (SamplerFilter): The filtering method to use for mipmaps. Default: 0.
Method: set_mip_filter(value: SamplerFilter)
Method: get_mip_filter() -> SamplerFilter

repeat_u (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode to use along the U axis of UV coordinates. This affects the returned values if sampling outside the UV bounds. Default: 2.
Method: set_repeat_u(value: SamplerRepeatMode)
Method: get_repeat_u() -> SamplerRepeatMode

repeat_v (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode to use along the V axis of UV coordinates. This affects the returned values if sampling outside the UV bounds. Default: 2.
Method: set_repeat_v(value: SamplerRepeatMode)
Method: get_repeat_v() -> SamplerRepeatMode

repeat_w (SamplerRepeatMode): The repeat mode to use along the W axis of UV coordinates. This affects the returned values if sampling outside the UV bounds. Only effective for 3D samplers. Default: 2.
Method: set_repeat_w(value: SamplerRepeatMode)
Method: get_repeat_w() -> SamplerRepeatMode

unnormalized_uvw (bool): If true, the texture will be sampled with coordinates ranging from 0 to the texture's resolution. Otherwise, the coordinates will be normalized and range from 0 to 1. Default: false.
Method: set_unnormalized_uvw(value: bool)
Method: get_unnormalized_uvw() -> bool

use_anisotropy (bool): If true, perform anisotropic sampling. See anisotropy_max. Default: false.
Method: set_use_anisotropy(value: bool)
Method: get_use_anisotropy() -> bool